conditions.value:
All studies in this meta-analysis employed a pre-post, within-subjects design. All participants provided saliva samples pre- and post-stressor and samples were assayed for at least one of the following biomarkers: IL-6, IL-1β, TNF-α, and/or IL-10. 
Already collected methodological information on stressor type will be reclassified into 1 = social evaluative stressor vs. 0 = any other type of stressor. We also coded whether studies used a resting baseline sample (0 = did not use a resting baseline, 1 = did use a resting baseline), average sample body mass index (BMI; continuous), percent of the sample that identifies as African-American (continuous), and percent of the sample that is college educated (continuous). These variables will not be reclassified.

hypothesis.value:
The purpose of this study is to examine various methodological, demographic, and health-related moderators of responses of salivary markers of inflammation (interleukin [IL]-6, IL-10, IL-1 beta [IL-1β], tumor necrosis factor alpha [TNF-α]) following exposure to acute stress. The proposed study will utilize secondary data analyses from a database collected as part of a larger meta-analysis (Szabo et al., 2020, under review) in order to further inform stress and salivary inflammation research.

The specific moderators we will assess include: stressor type (1 = social evaluative stressor vs. 0 = any other type of stressor), whether studies used a resting baseline sample (0 = did not use a resting baseline, 1 = did use a resting baseline), average sample body mass index (BMI), percent of the sample that identifies as African-American, and percent of the sample that is college educated. We will also provide a descriptive analysis showing the specific time points that each effect size was found for each biomarker within each study. 

Specifically, the hypotheses that we will test are: 
•	Social evaluative stressors will result in larger effect sizes for all biomarkers compared to stressors not using social evaluation
•	Studies that used a resting baseline sample will result in larger effect sizes for all biomarkers compared to those that do not.
•	Higher average sample BMI be associated with larger effect sizes for all biomarkers.
•	Samples with a higher percentage of African American individuals will result in larger effect sizes for all biomarkers. 
•	Samples with a lower percentage of college educated individuals will result in larger effect sizes for all biomarkers. 

Citation: Szabo, Y.Z., Slavish, D.C., Graham-Engeland, J.E. (revised & resubmitted). The effect of acute stress on salivary markers of inflammation: A systematic review and meta-analysis

attributes.title: Standardized pyrogen testing of health products with LAL (Limulusamebocyte lysate) as a substitute for rabbit pyrogen testing: A scoping review.
attributes.description: Project of a scoping review on the applicability of bacterial endotoxin test for health products.

summary.value: The Limulus Amebocyte Lysate test (LAL) is a method used to screen for gram - negative bacterial lipopolysaccharide (LPS) contamination in pharmaceutical products. In the 1980's the United States Food and Drug Administration (FDA) approved the LAL test as an alternative to the Rabbit Pyrogen Test (RPT), which was introduced in the 1940s. Both tests are still used across the World, with the LAL supplanting the RPT as the industry standard. However, it is now well established that LAL testing does not detect a broad range of biologically relevant pyrogens. Moreover, there are reported interferences that can limit its practical use for different health products. In this context, this project aims to assess the scientific literature and scope the evidence for the application of standardized LAL tests in different application domains within the full spectra of health products. The PRISMA Scr statement will be used to analyze those studies that evaluated health products from different domains of applicability for endotoxin contamination through LAL tests compared to RPT tests using standard protocols. A critical appraisal of the methodological quality of the evidence will be performed through the ToxRTool. Data will be collected regarding the use of standard protocols in the LAL and RPT tests, their sensitivities, the agreement or discrepancy of the results, the indication of interferents in the LAL tests and the solutions pointed out for these in each source of evidence.

attributes.title: Impression Management and the Dark Triad
attributes.description: Although studies show that Machiavellianism and other Dark Triad traits typically have a negative correlation with self-reported impression management. Further, most studies on impression management in the workplace have focused on how individuals seek to appear more competent. Here, we look at experimental changes in self-reported personality using a mock job application.

q2.value: Our hypothesis is that individuals high in Machiavellianism, but not psychopathy or narcissism, will show experimental differences in their self-reported personality when asked to fill out the survey as they would for a good position for a company in your field. Specifically, we predict that individuals high in Machiavellianism will report being HIGHER in Agentic values when applying for a job in a competitive field, and higher in communal values when applying for a job in a cooperative field. These patterns will not emerge for psychopathy, and probably not for narcissism either.

q3.value: Experiment - A researcher randomly assigns treatments to study subjects, this includes field or lab experiments. This is also known as an intervention experiment and includes randomized controlled trials.

value: No blinding is involved in this study.

Thus, there are TWO CONDITIONS - agentic and communal, b/t subjects. All will be told that this is a good job.

question.value: Cooperative vs. competitive work environment --- 2 group design

We will use the Short Dark Triad to operationalize Dark Triad and Values scale from Paulhus & Trapnell to operationalize circumplex values. Psychopathy subscale from Dirty Dozen Jonason webster to study a slice of dark personality. 10 item HH subscale from HEXACO to study Honesty /Humility. All appropriately scored and averaged into composites.

Hierarchical linear regression with contrast coded condition (1 competitive, -1 cooperative) interacting with each Dark Triad trait. We will do separate regressions for each Dark Triad trait, and we will do one big regression with all three Dark Triad traits (all will interact with condition)

q2.value: I expect there will be a main effect showing that high amounts of quarantine will lead to a higher anxiety level.  There will also be a main effect showing that high severity of Coronavirus (500 cases) will lead to a higher anxiety level.

q3.value: Experiment - A researcher randomly assigns treatments to study subjects, this includes field or lab experiments. This is also known as an intervention experiment and includes randomized controlled trials.

value: No blinding is involved in this study.

question.value: 2 (amount of quarantine) x 2 (severity of Coronavirus) between subject design

q8.value: Registration prior to accessing the data

question.value: I am posting a link to social media for participants to follow so they can fill out my survey. The survey includes demographics, asks the participants how many days total they have spent in quarantine and they are asked the last digit of their phone number, this leads them to scenario one or two. The scenarios show the severity of Coronavirus (high or low). Then, participants are asked to rate their anxiety level from 1-5.

q11.value: Ideally, I will have 20 per between-subject group, for a total of 80 participants.

q12.value: My professor said to get 20 participants per between-subject group.

q13.value: I plan to stop collecting data once I have at least 25 per cell or 100 total.

question.value:
The severity of Coronavirus: 
1.The government reports 50 confirmed positive cases of Coronavirus in your local area and 2. The government reports 500 confirmed positive cases of Coronavirus in your local area.

SV: Amount of days total spent in quarantine (low and High)
DV: anxiety levels
The numbers that the participants enter for days of quarantine, I will split it at the mean in order to classify it as low and high.
